Disable Yearly Developer Gifts.Description: This setting will disable the mod developer gifts you will receive yearly. By default, you will receive a yearly randomized gift from myself :-)

Crops Growth Speed.Description: Select the growth speed of all crops. This setting spans a range from 25% to 99% faster. Keep in mind that it will also impact the rate at which regrowable crops replenish themselves.

Crops All Seasons.Description: All crops are now capable of growing in any season.

Harvest With Scythe.Description: All crops can now be harvested with a scythe.

Crops Need No Water.Description: All crops will no longer need to be watered to grow.

Plant Crops Most Locations.Description: All crops can now be sown in a variety of locations, specifically those with tillable soil.

Auto Regrow Crops.Description: All crops will naturally regenerate without the need for replanting. This setting grants all crops the same regrowth effect as Strawberries, Blueberries, Hot Peppers, and Ancient Fruit, etc.

Crops Regrowth Speed.Description: Select the regrowth speed of crops after the initial harvest. These settings apply universally to all crops when the Auto Regrow Crops setting is enabled. However, if the Auto Regrow Crops setting is disabled, they will specifically impact the standard regrowable crops such as Strawberries, Blueberries, Hot Peppers, and Ancient Fruit, etc.

Crops Minimum Quality.Description: Select the minimum quality level for crop harvests. By default, this setting yields crops with no quality, indicated by the absence of stars. The 'Default' setting will be Gold for crops not using Deluxe Fertlizer and Iridium for crops using Deluxe Fertilizer.

Prismatic Seeds (REQ).Description: Prismatic Seeds, a novel seed item, are now obtainable through foraging and can be sown to yield Prismatic Shards. This configuration serves as a prerequisite for all Prismatic Seeds options below!

Craftable Prismatic Seeds.Description: Instead of a single seed, five seeds can be crafted into a bag of Prismatic Seeds item which can be planted for Prismatic Shards. Upon enabling this setting, you will automatically acquire the Prismatic Seeds crafting recipe at Farming Level 1. To activate this setting, ensure that the Prismatic Seeds (REQ) setting is enabled.

Prismatic Shards Growth Speed.Description: Select the growth speed of Prismatic Shards, with a range spanning from 25% to 99% faster. To activate this setting, ensure that the Prismatic Seeds (REQ) setting is enabled.

Regrow Prismatic Shards.Description: Prismatic Shards obtained from Prismatic Seeds will now regrow automatically, similar to Strawberries! To activate this setting, ensure that the Prismatic Seeds (REQ) setting is enabled.

Prismatic Shard Quality.Description: Prismatic Shards will now be assigned quality grades upon harvest, including silver, gold, and iridium, similar to regular crops.

Prismatic Shard Sell Value.Description: Select the sell value of Prismatic Shards, with the default set at 2000g. The range spans from 1750g to 1g. Please note, the sell values will only affect newly acquired Prismatic Shards after enabling the setting of your choosing. Scroll down for additional options.

Rare Prismatic Seeds.Description: Prismatic Seeds obtained from foraging will now spawn less frequently. To activate this setting, ensure that the Prismatic Seeds (REQ) setting is enabled.

Diggable Prismatic Seeds.Description: Prismatic Seeds will now have a chance to spawn from dig spots, with options for both 15% and 5% probabilities. To activate this setting, ensure that the Prismatic Seeds (REQ) setting is enabled.

Giant Prismatic Shards.Description: Prismatic Seeds now have the potential to develop into giant Prismatic Shards, similar to that of giant crops. To activate this setting, ensure that the Prismatic Seeds (REQ) setting is enabled.

Giant Prismatic Spawn Rate.Description: Select the likelihood of Prismatic Shards developing into giant Prismatic Shards, with a range spanning from 5% to 100% chance. To activate this setting, ensure that both the Prismatic Seeds (REQ) and Giant Prismatic Shards settings are enabled. Scroll down for additional options.
